name: delay
description: An entity that describes a time interval in the context of an experimental task.

unit.description: Units in standard international format to describe the time.

values.description: Duration value of the time passed during this delay. Can be int, float or` list of values

distribution.description: Name of the statistical distribution from which the values are drawn. If fixed_list then it is pregenerated

seed.description: Seed value chosen to fix the random number generator.

n_draws.description: Number of draws / samples picked from the random distribution. This is typically same as number of trials / use as a proxy for pregenerated or not
